# Coding Standards

## TypeScript

- Explicit type annotations on **every** property, variable, parameter, and return type (`@typescript-eslint/typedef`)
  - `public name: string = 'default';`
  - `const count: number = 0;`
  - `(event: MouseEvent) => ...`
  - `public getData(): Observable<User[]> { ... }`
  - `private readonly router: Router = inject(Router);`
  - `public user: InputSignal<UserData> = input.required<UserData>();`
  - `public selected: OutputEmitterRef<UserData> = output<UserData>();`
  - `public loadingSignal: WritableSignal<boolean> = signal<boolean>(false);`
  - `public readonly fullNameSignal: Signal<string> = computed<string>(() => ...);`
  - `public valueSignal: ModelSignal<string> = model<string>('');`
- Access modifiers (`public`, `private`) on every member - `protected` is NOT allowed
- No `any` - use proper interfaces or `unknown`
- Use utility types (`Partial`, `Pick`, `Omit`, `Record`) in interfaces

## Angular Patterns

- Standalone components only - no NgModules
- Do NOT set `standalone: true` in decorators (default since v19+)
- `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush` in every `@Component`
- Use `host` object instead of `@HostBinding` / `@HostListener`
- Use `class` / `style` bindings instead of `ngClass` / `ngStyle`
- Use `NgOptimizedImage` with `ngSrc` for static images (not inline base64)
- Prefer zoneless change detection (zone.js removed in v21)
- Lazy loading via `loadComponent()` for feature routes
- Use `resource()` or `httpResource()` for reactive async data fetching (experimental)

## Signals & State

- `input()`, `output()`, `model()` signal functions instead of decorators
- `computed()` for derived state
- `linkedSignal()` for dependent reactive state
- No `mutate` on signals - use `update` or `set`
- No NgRx - will be removed from the project
- Business logic in shared services, not components

### Signal Naming Convention

- Private signals: no `Signal` postfix
- Public signals: must have `Signal` postfix, e.g. `public readonly itemsSignal: WritableSignal<PageHeaderAction[]> = signal([]);`

## Templates

- Native control flow (`@if`, `@for`, `@switch`) - no `*ngIf` / `*ngFor` / `*ngSwitch`
- `@let` for template-local variables
- No arrow functions in templates
- `async` pipe for observables
- Keep template logic simple

## Services

- `inject()` instead of constructor injection
- `providedIn: 'root'` for singletons
- Single responsibility - business logic in services

## RxJS

- No nested subscriptions - use `switchMap` and similar operators
- Always handle unsubscription - prefer `takeUntilDestroyed()`
- `BehaviorSubject` / `ReplaySubject` preferred over `Subject` when current value is needed

## Forms

- Prefer Signal Forms (`form()` + `[formField]`) (experimental v21)
- Custom validators in a shared file
- Validation messages near fields

## API Communication

- `httpResource()` for reactive data fetching where applicable (experimental)
- `catchError` with user-friendly messages
- Interceptors for authorization, errors, and default limit (`9999`)

## Security

- No `[innerHTML]` without `DomSanitizer`
- Frontend validation present
- Guards for role-based permissions

## Styles

- BEM methodology
- No `!important` or `::ng-deep`
- Use `@use`, `@mixin`, `@include`
- Colors in `colors.scss`; shared typography styles
- Scoped styles only

## Translation

- Always use `translate` pipe or `translate.instant()` with translation keys
- Check existing shared groups before adding new keys

## Unit Testing — MANDATORY

- Karma/Jasmine with Angular TestBed
- Every `*.service.ts` and `*.component.ts` MUST have a `*.spec.ts` file — no exceptions
- A PR that adds/modifies a service or component without updating its spec file MUST be rejected
- Minimum 80% branch coverage; target 100% for services
- Use `jasmine.createSpyObj<T>()` with explicit generic types — no `any` in tests
- Use `NO_ERRORS_SCHEMA` to avoid deep rendering of child components
- Run: `ng test --no-watch --browsers=ChromeHeadless`

## E2E Testing — MANDATORY

- Playwright with Page Object Model (POM) pattern
- Every new user-facing flow MUST have E2E coverage
- Tests: `tests/e2e/tests/*.spec.ts`, Page objects: `tests/e2e/page-objects/*.ts`
- Run: `npm run e2e:quiz`

## Accessibility

- Must pass all AXE checks
- WCAG AA compliance: focus management, color contrast, ARIA attributes
- Consider Angular Aria for accessible headless components

## Class Member Ordering

1. **Signal I/O**: `input()`, `output()`, `model()`
2. **Injected deps**: `inject()` calls
3. **Properties**: public then private (`readonly` and `signal()` grouped within access modifier)
4. **Lifecycle**: `constructor()` -> `ngOnInit()` (with `effect()`) -> other hooks -> `ngOnDestroy()`
5. **Methods**: getters/setters -> public -> template-accessible -> private helpers

### Import Ordering

1. Angular libraries (`@angular/core`, `@angular/common`, etc.)
2. Third-party libraries (RxJS, Angular Material, etc.)
3. Project modules/services/components (relative paths)
4. Other items
5. Local enums and types
